column2: Enable internal access to NAT instance: receive internet-bound traffic from instances in private subnet, as well as SSH traffic from vpc
can contain only alphanumeric characters, spaces, dashes and underscores.
must be a valid CIDR range of the form x.x.x.x/x.

[{u'ToPort': u'80', u'IpProtocol': u'tcp', u'CidrIp': u'0.0.0.0/0', u'FromPort': u'80'}, {u'ToPort': u'443', u'IpProtocol': u'tcp', u'CidrIp': u'0.0.0.0/0', u'FromPort': u'443'}, {u'ToPort': u'-1', u'IpProtocol': u'icmp', u'CidrIp': u'0.0.0.0/0', u'FromPort': u'-1'}]
VPC ID of newly created VPC

[{u'Value': {u'Ref': u'AWS::StackName'}, u'Key': u'Application'}, {u'Value': u'Public', u'Key': u'Network'}]
